#
# Testing the API for cairo in ATS
#
# Author: Hongwei Xi (hwxi AT cs DOT bu DOT edu)
# Start Time: December, 2009
#

######

The TEST directory contains a list of cairo examples:

cairo-test1-1.dats: Hello, world!
cairo-test1-2.dats: A cairo digital clock based on GTK
cairo-test2.dats: drawing a rounded rectangle
cairo-test3.dats: drawing a filled regular pentagon
cairo-test4.dats: drawing a Koch (fractal) curve
cairo-test5.dats: drawing a negative arc
cairo-test6.dats: clipping
cairo-test7-1.dats: drawing a (still) clock
cairo-test7-2.dats: drawing a functioning analog clock (with GTK interface)
cairo-test8-1.dats: Kitaoka's famous image of illusory circular motion
cairo-test8-2.dats: A variant of [cairo-test8-1.dats] based on Xlib
cairo-test8-3.dats: A variant of [cairo-test8-1.dats] based on GTK
cairo-test9.dats: A wavy illusion (with GTK interface)
cairo-test11.dats: an example testing two filling rules
cairo-test12.dats: an example involving radial pattern (gradient)
cairo-test13.dats: an example testing line cap styles
cairo-test14.dats: an example testing line joint styles
cairo-test15.dats: an example testing text filling
cairo-test16.dats: an example testing text alignment

There is also a [Makefile] for generating executable binaries.

####### end of [README] ######
